Below are the commands commonly used in Linux environment/machine

1. ls --> List out all the files and folders in the current directory
2. cd <directory> --> change the current directory
3. mkdir <directory name>  --> Create new directory
4. touch <filename>  --> Create a new file in the current directory.
5. vim <filename>  --> Open a file in editor. Vim is the default editor in Linux.
6. After opening a file in Vim editor use the "Insert" key to add code to the file. once you complete use "Esc" key and then type ":w" to save the changes
7. lsof -i :5000  --> This command will list out the program which uses this port "5000"
8. if you want to kill the program and release the port use this command "kill -9 <PID>"



